"""PART II Entitlement and amount

4A. Meaning of “qualifying young person”

(1)

(b)

Editorial note: current text valid from 2025-03-21.

A person who has reached the age of 16 but not the age of 20 is a qualifying young person for the purposes of these Regulations—

up to, but not including, the 1st September following the person's 19th birthday, if the person is enrolled on, or accepted for, approved training or a course of education—

(i)

which is not a course of advanced education within the meaning of regulation 12(3) of the Universal Credit Regulations 2013;"""

qualifying_young_person_lower_age_4A_1_b:
    entity: Person
    period: Day
    dtype: Integer
    from 2025-03-21:
        16

qualifying_young_person_upper_age_4A_1_b:
    entity: Person
    period: Day
    dtype: Integer
    from 2025-03-21:
        20

qualifying_young_person_nineteenth_birthday_age_4A_1_b:
    entity: Person
    period: Day
    dtype: Integer
    from 2025-03-21:
        19

person_age:
    entity: Person
    period: Day
    dtype: Integer

person_is_enrolled_on_or_accepted_for_approved_training_or_course_of_education:
    entity: Person
    period: Day
    dtype: Boolean

day_is_before_1st_september_following_person_19th_birthday:
    entity: Person
    period: Day
    dtype: Boolean

course_is_not_advanced_education_within_meaning_of_regulation_12_3_of_the_universal_credit_regulations_2013:
    entity: Person
    period: Day
    dtype: Boolean

qualifying_young_person_4A_1_b_i:
    entity: Person
    period: Day
    dtype: Boolean
    from 2025-03-21:
        person_age >= qualifying_young_person_lower_age_4A_1_b and person_age < qualifying_young_person_upper_age_4A_1_b and day_is_before_1st_september_following_person_19th_birthday and person_is_enrolled_on_or_accepted_for_approved_training_or_course_of_education and course_is_not_advanced_education_within_meaning_of_regulation_12_3_of_the_universal_credit_regulations_2013
